history.text: Hi, how are you?
Hello! How are you today?
I'm great, thanks for asking.
I am good too!
Have you seen Batman VS Superman?
I have not, how was it?
It was absolutely awful, I honestly don't recommend seeing it at all.
Hm, I wasn't expecting that. The last one I watched was the one with Heath Ledger in it. Why was it awful?
I think the story overall was poorly done. When you think Batman VS Superman you think it's two heros one on one, it just wasn't that at all.
Right, I would think they would work together. Were they enemies?
The story does begin that way, which makes you think it would lead up to them fighting throughout the movie. However, it was massively derailed with the guest appearance of wonder woman.
Oh I see, my daughter loves wonder woman actually. Was it safe for children or pretty graphic?
Lex Luthor is laughable bad in te film as well
That's a shame
How old we talking?
She's 7
I wouldn't let my 7 year old watch it, it's pretty violent.
I'll take your word for it, it wasn't something I was interested in when it came out. I usually watch mostly all of the new movies but it didn't look that great
I imagine I would have the same opinion as you after watching it
Yeahm I think they dropped the ball on this movie. They tried to do too many things at once.
It's almost like they had three different plots and combined them all into this mess.
It sounds that way, maybe they were trying to set up the wonder woman movie and get more people interested in that
Who played Batman and Spiderman?

Ben Affleck playe
d Batman and Henry Cavill reprised his role as superman.
I think they both did good, but they just didn't have a good story to really follow.
Ok, I do remember that.. I don't really care for Ben Affleck
I am not a big fan of his either. I thought he would be a very bad fit for the character.
That's the same thing I thought.
He was surprisingly good, I think he plays Bruce better than Batman but he does well regardless.
Even the critics didn't like the movie.
It recieved pretty bad scores across the board.
That doesn't surprise me at all, after it came out I didn't even hear any of my friends talking about the movie
I don't think I would go see it.
I wouldn't waste your time, if you do see it. It will be because it's on local TV
I'm going to head out. Have a good rest of your day!
You too, thank you

uid2response.feedback: This movie wasn't something I was interested in watching before talking about it, the other person sealed the deal for me though.
